where $\Delta_{\rm EW} (\rm max)$ is the maximal fine-tuning one wants to allow. For example,
if we take $\Delta_{\rm EW}$= 20, with $\tan\beta$=10, we can have $m_{A}$ roughly as large as 4 TeV. This is why we see that 
